:: Chapter1.1 {"position":"850,325","size":"100,100"}
<div align='center' style='font-size: 300%;'>\
    Chapter 1 - Mercury Lights. \
</div>

<img src="https://i.imgur.com/KEHgvMH.png" alt="Smoking">
The view of the green mercury light made me feel nauseous. I couldn’t believe it was already spring, it passed so quickly. Back then time seemed to move both faster and slower at the same time, like a broken clock. 

GIF—---------------------------1:2-GIF-----------------------------GIF

The bar was crowded. It was a late Tuesday night. Outside the air was fresh, the smell of fallen rain mixed with the smell of tobacco and beer. Music blared from the inside. Awful, awful music.
Smoke escaped my mouth in thick clouds, and as the cloud evaporated a hand fell on my arm. 

GIF—---------------------------1:3-GIF-----------------------------GIF

It was Nicole. She joined me for a smoke and we stood there for a while, observing the greenly lit street and the wet concrete. Nicole usually didn’t smoke, it was just for the occasion. Or maybe she never quit like she said she did, all that time ago. 
“You good?” Nicole said, breaking the silence.
“It's just, you know the music and everything, it gets overwhelming. My instincts are telling me to just run away.” I said.
Nicole gently squeezed my arm. 
“Well, the music is shit anyway,” she said as she took a drag from her cigarette. 
It was disgusting, but she looked cool so who cares. 
There was a fractional pause in the flow of the world, where the streetlights stopped their static humming and the smoke froze.


