:: Chapter1.2 {"position":"850,450","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/VA9K2rm.png" alt="Something">

Apartments stretched endlessly. A strong light burned on the other side of my eyelids. Yesterday's memories greeted me as I opened my eyes. It was a pleasant evening, uneventful and not too interesting, like I preferred it. 
I got up to make some coffee in the small kitchen on the other side of the living room. Taking a quick peek out the window, I saw that the sun was blaring outside. 
 The endless stacks of books had started to spread to the kitchen. It had started to become more difficult to walk around the apartement. 
I heard a muffled “Hey!” from the living room, 
“Ash are you making coffee?”, I imagine Nicole snuggled up in thick blankets. 
“You want some?” I answered. 
“Of course I want some!” the voice echoed playfully, “And I'm awake, promise!” 
Her promises have always been more theoretical, nothing more than a word, or a string of words. I didn’t mind too much, I did the same for a lot of things. 

GIF—---------------------------1:5-GIF-----------------------------GIF

While I waited for the coffee to set in the French press, I felt my worries catching up. The thoughts tasted bitter. The classic mental dribble followed, what to bring for lunch, what to forget to bring. You can’t eat cigarettes. As usual, I would most likely settle for sandwiches.
A rustle came from the bedroom, slash office, slash living room. The beast had awoken. Sometimes, her presence was the only thing that could break my chain of thoughts.
“When are you going to get a TV or something?” Nicole said as she walked into the kitchen in pajamas.
“I have a computer, isn't that enough?” 
“That's from the 70s! And besides, you have internet speed from 2005.”
“None of those numbers makes any sense,” I said, pouring coffee into two big cups- one black, and one white. 
“Gosh, it's like you're such an old person.” Nicole sat down at the table with a grin. “At least, please get a Bluetooth speaker or something!”
“Hey now, that's unfair, I got the radio. It plays classical music, and sometimes tells the weather.”

GIF—---------------------------1:6-GIF-----------------------------GIF

Nicole looked at me with a gleeful expression. “No, I mean so you can like, hook up your phone and stuff dude.” I smiled back. We both knew it was never going to happen.
We sat for a while, enjoying the morning sun, silence, hot coffee, and each other's company. I had exams to study for, so I needed to stay focused. Nicole grabbed my hand and time stopped.  
 “Hey,” I said.
 
GIF—---------------------------1:7-GIF-----------------------------GIF

 “What?” we locked eyes. 
 “That's my coffee-drinking hand.” 
 “Use your other hand, I heard it's good for your brain!” 
I awkwardly grabbed the cup with the other hand and took a sip. It made me feel dumb rather than smart. 
“Do you feel smarter yet?” 
“Not one bit.” 
 We both laughed, and I forgot my worries.
 
